article.headline: South Carolina St. 89, Winston-Salem St. 82
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Brian Mason scored 19 points and pulled down 16 rebounds to lead South Carolina State to a 89-82 win over Winston-Salem State on Friday night. The Bulldogs (13-16) stretched a five-point halftime lead into a 48-38 advantage with 13:39 to go. The Rams (5-24) wouldn't get closer than five the rest of the way. South Carolina State won the game at the foul line, making 35 of 43 free throws. Winston-Salem State shot 19-of-25 from the foul line. The Bulldogs outrebounded the Rams 44-36. South Carolina State will play in the Mid-Eastern Conference tournament next week, while the season has ended for Winston-Salem State. Darrell Wonge led the Rams with 24 points, while Norman Carter added 15 points and 10 rebounds. Robert Baker added 19 points for the Bulldogs.
